version: 4
annotations:
  - {"kind":"user","id":"7db1bf91-b301-4636-bfc3-3d25cf7e4bb0","permanentBaseCommit":"c936564fd70308985755515226f0fed4c61769c7","message":"I would have expected us to already have a load companion function somewhere.","preset":"%Q","scope":"line","anchor":{"line":198,"text":"async function loadCompanion(file: string, records: Map<string, AnnotationCompanion>): Promise<AnnotationCompanion> {","before":["\t\t}","\t}","}"],"after":["\tconst loaded = records.get(file);","\tif (loaded !== undefined) { return loaded; }","\ttry {"]},"officialResponses":[{"userAnnotationId":"7db1bf91-b301-4636-bfc3-3d25cf7e4bb0","agentId":"0ed1fae4-3341-433f-8fa6-63ad8ff1e3f9","agentSessionId":"623920cb-072f-4e0b-a0c3-9e7ac395db33","body":"Yes—your expectation is correct. The repository already has companion-reading code, and the selected `loadCompanion` is substantially duplicating one of the existing helpers.\n\nThere are three relevant functions:\n\n1. **`readCompanionFile`** in `packages/cli/src/annotations.ts:618`\n   - Reads and parses a companion through `parseAnnotationCompanion`.\n   - It is exported and is the general reader used by annotation append/read/delete/response operations.\n   - It deliberately treats `ENOENT` as “no companion yet” and synthesizes an empty `AnnotationCompanion`, deriving its source digest when necessary.\n   - It does not accept or populate a per-operation cache.\n\n2. **`requireCompanion`** in `packages/cli/src/annotations.ts:455`\n   - Checks a `Map<string, AnnotationCompanion>` cache first.\n   - Reads, parses, and caches the exact existing companion otherwise.\n   - Treats a missing linked companion as an error rather than synthesizing an empty one.\n   - It is private to `annotations.ts` and is used when re-anchoring reciprocal links.\n\n3. **`loadCompanion`** at the selected location in `packages/cli/src/companionRepair.ts:199`\n   - Also checks the same kind of cache, then reads, parses, and caches an existing companion.\n   - Also rejects a missing linked companion.\n   - Its material difference is error classification: it translates `ENOENT` into `GitWorkflowConflictError('companion_repair_conflict', ...)`, which the Git repair workflow understands as a repair conflict.\n\nTherefore, directly replacing `loadCompanion` with `readCompanionFile` would be incorrect: a missing reciprocal companion must abort repair, not become an empty companion. But `loadCompanion` and `requireCompanion` are nearly the same strict, cache-aware operation and are reasonable consolidation candidates.\n\nA clean shared boundary would be an exported strict reader such as `requireExistingCompanion(companionPath, records)` that reads/parses/caches and preserves or reports absence. The repair caller could then translate a missing-file error into `GitWorkflowConflictError`, while re-anchoring could retain its own domain error. Alternatively, the shared helper could accept an error factory, though that would couple the low-level reader more closely to callers.\n\nOne small signal of the duplication is that `requireCompanion` currently accepts `_cwd` but does not use it. Both strict helpers independently implement the same cache lookup, `readFile`, parse, cache insertion, and `ENOENT` handling.\n\nSo the conclusion is: **an existing general reader does exist, and an existing strict cached reader also exists; the repair-local helper is justified only by its repair-specific error type, not by a fundamentally different loading operation.** Consolidating the strict loading primitive would reduce duplication without changing missing-file semantics.\n\nNo source files were changed. Validation consisted of read-only inspection of the three helpers, their call sites, error types, Git repair tests, and the current diff. No tests were run because this was a code-structure question; there is no blocker.\n","createdAt":"2026-07-21T21:57:33.571Z"}],"agentAnnotations":[]}
  - {"kind":"user","id":"01a5719b-c84a-403c-9216-08faae362631","permanentBaseCommit":"c936564fd70308985755515226f0fed4c61769c7","message":"Please annotate the code so I can quickly review your findings.","preset":"%Q","scope":"line","anchor":{"line":198,"text":"async function loadCompanion(file: string, records: Map<string, AnnotationCompanion>): Promise<AnnotationCompanion> {","before":["\t\t}","\t}","}"],"after":["\tconst loaded = records.get(file);","\tif (loaded !== undefined) { return loaded; }","\ttry {"]},"officialResponses":[{"userAnnotationId":"01a5719b-c84a-403c-9216-08faae362631","agentId":"0ed1fae4-3341-433f-8fa6-63ad8ff1e3f9","agentSessionId":"623920cb-072f-4e0b-a0c3-9e7ac395db33","body":"Added a review annotation at `packages/cli/src/companionRepair.ts:199` summarizing the loader findings:\n\n- `loadCompanion` duplicates the cache-aware strict-loading behavior of `requireCompanion` in `packages/cli/src/annotations.ts`.\n- `readCompanionFile` cannot directly replace it because that general reader synthesizes an empty companion on `ENOENT`, whereas repair must reject a missing linked companion with `GitWorkflowConflictError('companion_repair_conflict', ...)`.\n- The annotation recommends extracting a shared strict/cache-aware reader and keeping domain-specific missing-file error translation at the caller.\n\nNo source code was changed. Validation consisted of re-reading all three current helper implementations and confirming that the annotation command succeeded. Tests were not run because this was a review-only annotation; there is no blocker.\n","createdAt":"2026-07-21T22:01:33.619Z"}],"agentAnnotations":[{"annotationId":"agent-406c6fde5f41e9aff383607e0eca0d84","file":"packages/cli/src/companionRepair.ts","line":198}]}
  - {"kind":"agent","id":"agent-406c6fde5f41e9aff383607e0eca0d84","agentId":"0ed1fae4-3341-433f-8fa6-63ad8ff1e3f9","agentSessionId":"623920cb-072f-4e0b-a0c3-9e7ac395db33","permanentBaseCommit":"c936564fd70308985755515226f0fed4c61769c7","body":"**Review finding — duplicate strict companion loader.** `annotations.ts` already contains `requireCompanion` (around line 455), which performs the same cache lookup, read, parse, cache insertion, and missing-linked-file rejection. The exported `readCompanionFile` is not a direct substitute because it intentionally synthesizes an empty companion on `ENOENT`; repair must instead report `GitWorkflowConflictError('companion_repair_conflict', ...)`. Consider extracting one shared strict/cache-aware reader and translating absence into the caller-specific error, rather than retaining both private implementations.\n","createdAt":"2026-07-21T22:01:10.993Z","anchor":{"line":198,"text":"async function loadCompanion(file: string, records: Map<string, AnnotationCompanion>): Promise<AnnotationCompanion> {","before":["\t\t}","\t}","}"],"after":["\tconst loaded = records.get(file);","\tif (loaded !== undefined) { return loaded; }","\ttry {"]},"userAnnotation":{"annotationId":"01a5719b-c84a-403c-9216-08faae362631","file":"packages/cli/src/companionRepair.ts","line":198}}
